8
00:02:05,250 --> 00:02:09,310
You do whatever you want. You could get sued!

9
00:02:09,310 --> 00:02:12,060
Yes, sue me if you want.

10
00:02:12,060 --> 00:02:14,090
But they probably won't accept the case.

11
00:02:14,090 --> 00:02:18,210
Because I didn't do it alone. We did it together.

12
00:02:18,210 --> 00:02:20,310
W-What do you mean we did it together?

13
00:02:20,310 --> 00:02:22,180
Wow, you're so unbelievable.

14
00:02:22,180 --> 00:02:25,230
I wasn't thinking and didn't do anything, and you did it all by yourself.

15
00:02:25,230 --> 00:02:28,030
Oppa, you weren't thinking and didn't do anything?

16
00:02:28,030 --> 00:02:33,550
You were 0.0001mm close to me as if you'd kiss me.

17
00:02:33,550 --> 00:02:36,360
Gosh, seriously.

18
00:02:36,360 --> 00:02:38,400
What are you, a turtle?

19
00:02:38,400 --> 00:02:43,080
I just did it because you were approaching me too slowly.

20
00:02:43,080 --> 00:02:45,060
You should be thanking me instead.

21
00:02:45,060 --> 00:02:47,540
W-What did you say?

22
00:02:47,540 --> 00:02:51,160
Wow, she's framing me and writing a novel now.

23
00:02:51,160 --> 00:02:54,610
When did I get as close as 0.0001mm from you?

24
00:02:54,610 --> 00:02:56,590
Oppa, try to be honest.

25
00:02:56,590 --> 00:03:00,030
Your heart was racing earlier because you liked me.

26
00:03:00,030 --> 00:03:02,530
Do you know how loud your heartbeat was?

27
00:03:02,530 --> 00:03:06,610
And your eyes were fired up as if you'd eat me alive.

28
00:03:06,610 --> 00:03:08,780
What was with those eyes?

29
00:03:08,780 --> 00:03:11,100
I can't believe you're framing me like this.

30
00:03:11,100 --> 00:03:13,710
Are you blaming me after stealing a kiss from me?

31
00:03:13,710 --> 00:03:16,370
What? I looked at you as if I'd eat you alive?

32
00:03:16,370 --> 00:03:18,190
What are you, a rabbit? Why would I eat you alive?

33
00:03:18,190 --> 00:03:19,870
Whatever.

34
00:03:19,870 --> 00:03:24,310
I'm letting this slide because we need to finish "Straightforward Romance" without issues.

35
00:03:24,310 --> 00:03:26,190
But if you steal a kiss from me again,

36
00:03:26,190 --> 00:03:29,320
there's no "Straightforward Romance" or anything, then. Got it?

37
00:03:31,090 --> 00:03:34,520
How much longer will you hide your feelings, Oppa?

38
00:03:35,360 --> 00:03:37,450
You came here because of me.

39
00:03:37,450 --> 00:03:39,290
Because I was meeting with President Gong.

40
00:03:39,290 --> 00:03:42,230
You got jealous because I was with another man.

41
00:03:42,230 --> 00:03:44,570
Because you like me.

42
00:03:44,570 --> 00:03:46,620
I definitely said it wasn't like that.

43
00:03:46,620 --> 00:03:48,610
I was in the area because of work.

44
00:03:48,610 --> 00:03:51,380
So, don't interpret it the way you want.

45
00:03:54,280 --> 00:03:56,040
For work?

46
00:03:56,040 --> 00:03:59,610
Yeah, right. You expect me to believe that?

47
00:04:00,510 --> 00:04:03,060
I know for sure now.

48
00:04:03,060 --> 00:04:05,850
That he likes me, too.

49
00:04:24,910 --> 00:04:26,350
What?

50
00:04:27,130 --> 00:04:29,770
What kind of stupid dream was that?

51
00:04:29,770 --> 00:04:32,210
Why would I have a dream like that?

52
00:04:34,230 --> 00:04:39,160
Did I kiss her back like she said?

53
00:04:40,530 --> 00:04:44,230
No, no. There's no way I did.

54
00:04:52,740 --> 00:04:54,500
Get it together, Go Pil Sung.

55
00:04:54,500 --> 00:04:56,780
What are you thinking right now?

56
00:04:56,780 --> 00:04:58,780
You can't do this.

57
00:05:00,970 --> 00:05:02,570
Yes.

58
00:05:03,770 --> 00:05:06,310
I can no longer get tempted by Do Ra.

59
00:05:07,480 --> 00:05:09,330
Not anymore.

60
00:05:17,310 --> 00:05:19,010
Do you...

61
00:05:20,600 --> 00:05:26,640
even remember what you said drunkenly last night?

62
00:05:27,470 --> 00:05:31,330
Yes, I remember everything, Hyungnim.

63
00:05:32,530 --> 00:05:36,900
I might as well be honest with you about everything.

64
00:05:39,780 --> 00:05:42,890
Okay, go ahead.

65
00:05:43,550 --> 00:05:48,420
I've been very disappointed in you, Hyungnim.

66
00:05:49,220 --> 00:05:51,740
I'm not even asking for what's yours.

67
00:05:51,740 --> 00:05:57,340
I'm asking for... what Father let me inherit, the Angel Investment.

68
00:05:57,340 --> 00:05:59,690
Why won't you give it to me?

69
00:06:00,560 --> 00:06:05,020
How long do I have to walk on eggshells and wonder when you'd give it to me?

70
00:06:06,010 --> 00:06:08,140
I want what's mine.

71
00:06:08,140 --> 00:06:10,990
Why do I have to tiptoe around you?

72
00:06:14,290 --> 00:06:17,330
Did I say I wouldn't give it to you?

73
00:06:17,330 --> 00:06:19,670
I'd give it to you if you were trustworthy.

74
00:06:19,670 --> 00:06:23,090
When will you finally trust me? When, exactly?

75
00:06:23,090 --> 00:06:25,140
Do you really have to ask?

76
00:06:25,140 --> 00:06:28,250
What happened to the construction company I gave you?

77
00:06:28,250 --> 00:06:30,130
I kept saying no,

78
00:06:30,130 --> 00:06:35,450
but you insisted on building condos in Vietnam and Myanmar and gave up in the end.

79
00:06:35,450 --> 00:06:38,750
The whole company could've been in danger because of you.

80
00:06:38,750 --> 00:06:44,530
And how could I let you have Angel Investment after that?

81
00:06:45,370 --> 00:06:47,290
Wait a little longer.

82
00:06:47,890 --> 00:06:49,720
No, I don't want to.

83
00:06:49,720 --> 00:06:51,760
I can't wait, either.

84
00:06:51,760 --> 00:06:54,070
Give it to me now.

85
00:06:54,070 --> 00:06:55,750
What?

86
00:06:55,750 --> 00:06:58,440
What do you think you're doing?

87
00:07:00,870 --> 00:07:03,510
Give it to Jin Dan right now.

88
00:07:05,040 --> 00:07:08,010
Angel Investment is Jin Dan's.

89
00:07:08,010 --> 00:07:11,800
It's up to him whether he'd ruin or sell it.

90
00:07:11,800 --> 00:07:13,750
Why are you holding onto it?

91
00:07:13,750 --> 00:07:15,830
- Auntie. 
 - What?

92
00:07:15,830 --> 00:07:18,720
Did your wife tell you to hold onto it?

93
00:07:18,720 --> 00:07:24,160
Auntie, we're talking about Jin Dan. Why would you bring up Soo Yeon?

94
00:07:24,160 --> 00:07:25,670
Why are you doing this, Auntie?

95
00:07:25,670 --> 00:07:28,220
Just look at how this family is.

96
00:07:28,220 --> 00:07:31,470
I'm frustrated and angry, that's why.

97
00:07:31,470 --> 00:07:34,140
Same with Ma Ri and Jin Dan.

98
00:07:34,140 --> 00:07:36,910
You think it's something you can just insist on?

99
00:07:36,910 --> 00:07:40,400
Give it to Jin Dan and sort things out.

100
00:07:47,540 --> 00:07:50,100
You're giving him Angel Investment?

101
00:07:50,100 --> 00:07:52,890
Would you really be okay?

102
00:07:53,440 --> 00:07:57,450
Thinking about it, I think Auntie is right.

103
00:07:58,530 --> 00:08:00,550
Angel Investment.

104
00:08:01,230 --> 00:08:04,410
I can't continue to be responsible for it.

105
00:08:07,010 --> 00:08:09,270
If something goes wrong with it,

106
00:08:09,270 --> 00:08:11,570
the company and the subsidiary companies will suffer, too.

107
00:08:11,570 --> 00:08:14,630
We own its shares, too.

108
00:08:15,500 --> 00:08:19,550
But there's no choice anymore. It's no longer mine.

109
00:08:20,180 --> 00:08:24,530
We'd just have to trust him and keep an eye on it.

110
00:08:24,530 --> 00:08:30,610
And it doesn't look good to fight about stuff like this.

111
00:08:30,610 --> 00:08:34,280
It's better to let go of it at this stage.

112
00:08:35,620 --> 00:08:38,780
Okay, I understand.

113
00:08:40,830 --> 00:08:42,580
I'll get going.

114
00:08:48,450 --> 00:08:49,730
Is it true?

115
00:08:49,730 --> 00:08:51,850
Is he really giving it to you?

116
00:08:51,850 --> 00:08:55,040
Yes, he said he'd process it immediately.

117
00:08:55,040 --> 00:08:57,940
I'm Angel Investment's real CEO now.

118
00:08:57,940 --> 00:09:01,220
Gosh, Jin Dan! What in the world!

119
00:09:01,220 --> 00:09:03,910
Is this a dream or reality?

120
00:09:03,910 --> 00:09:05,970
By the way, do you think he actually will?

121
00:09:05,970 --> 00:09:08,500
What if he changes his mind later?

122
00:09:08,500 --> 00:09:10,200
Come on, Mom.

123
00:09:10,200 --> 00:09:13,380
He's a man of his word, you know.

124
00:09:13,380 --> 00:09:14,650
I suppose.

125
00:09:14,650 --> 00:09:17,700
Gosh, I can't believe this day finally came.

126
00:09:17,700 --> 00:09:20,390
Jin Dan, let's move out of this house, then.

127
00:09:20,390 --> 00:09:23,670
Let's move out and try living freely, okay?

128
00:09:23,670 --> 00:09:26,530
Mom, what are you talking about?

129
00:09:26,530 --> 00:09:28,940
Why would we move out?

130
00:09:28,940 --> 00:09:33,250
Do you think I came this far just to get Angel Investment?

131
00:09:33,950 --> 00:09:38,610
APP Group's successor, the chairman position is still left.

132
00:09:38,610 --> 00:09:41,810
Gosh, Jin Dan. Someone might hear you. Talk quietly.

133
00:09:41,810 --> 00:09:45,880
So, don't try to move out of this house, Mom.

134
00:09:45,880 --> 00:09:47,890
We're just getting started.

135
00:09:47,890 --> 00:09:51,130
Okay, I got it. Let's do that.

136
00:09:51,130 --> 00:09:54,890
I didn't even know you had a plan like that.

137
00:09:54,890 --> 00:09:58,690
Jin Dan, I'll only count on you from now on.

138
00:09:58,690 --> 00:10:01,450
Didn't you before? I'll get going now.

139
00:10:01,450 --> 00:10:03,470
Gosh, my handsome son.

140
00:10:03,470 --> 00:10:07,500
Have a nice day, handsome President Gong.

141
00:10:07,500 --> 00:10:11,110
Right, take good care of Auntie.

142
00:10:11,110 --> 00:10:15,140
Okay, okay. I understand what you mean.

143
00:10:20,640 --> 00:10:23,230
Auntie, thank you so much.

144
00:10:23,230 --> 00:10:26,570
You let us have Angel Investment.

145
00:10:27,300 --> 00:10:30,270
I'll never forget that.

146
00:10:30,270 --> 00:10:35,190
I'll think of you as my mother from now on.

147
00:10:35,190 --> 00:10:38,280
If you say blue is red,

148
00:10:38,280 --> 00:10:43,720
I'll think of blue as red and care for you for the rest of my life.

149
00:10:43,720 --> 00:10:46,840
 Hold on, why didn't I think of this? 

150
00:10:46,840 --> 00:10:50,570
 She and Soo Yeon were high school classmates. 

151
00:10:52,420 --> 00:10:57,430
Do you really mean what you just said?

152
00:10:57,430 --> 00:11:00,290
You'd think of me as your mother?

153
00:11:00,290 --> 00:11:04,560
You'd believe blue is red if I said so?

154
00:11:04,560 --> 00:11:07,810
Yes, Auntie. I mean it.

155
00:11:07,810 --> 00:11:12,450
You changed Jin Dan and my fate. There's nothing I can't do.

156
00:11:12,450 --> 00:11:15,910
I'll live for you for the rest of my life.

157
00:11:17,270 --> 00:11:21,210
If so, have a seat here.

158
00:11:21,210 --> 00:11:25,440
There's something I want to discuss quietly.

159
00:11:25,440 --> 00:11:27,710
Discuss?

160
00:11:27,710 --> 00:11:30,030
Tell me, Auntie.

161
00:11:31,400 --> 00:11:36,740
You know you can't reveal the mother and child's secret, right?

162
00:11:36,740 --> 00:11:38,720
Of course.

163
00:11:38,720 --> 00:11:42,050
You're telling me since you think of me as your child.

164
00:11:42,050 --> 00:11:46,660
I have to take everything you said to the grave.

165
00:11:48,320 --> 00:11:53,500
If so, find out about Ma Ri's mom's past.

166
00:11:53,500 --> 00:11:56,390
Her past before she married Jin Taek.

167
00:11:56,390 --> 00:11:58,280
Pardon?

168
00:11:58,280 --> 00:12:03,430
M-Ma Ri's mom, so Soo Yeon's past?

169
00:12:14,220 --> 00:12:15,700
I'm home.

170
00:12:15,700 --> 00:12:17,910
Oh, hey.

171
00:12:19,030 --> 00:12:21,690
Hey, what's that?

172
00:12:21,690 --> 00:12:25,400
I got traditional medicine made for Hyeon Cheol.

173
00:12:25,400 --> 00:12:27,860
I told him to rest, but he won't listen.

174
00:12:27,860 --> 00:12:32,650
I'm worried he'd get hurt doing physical work at his age.

175
00:12:32,650 --> 00:12:38,570
You did a good thing, but... don't you ever worry about me?

176
00:12:38,570 --> 00:12:44,750
Putting 300 eyes on the stuffed animal... is a tough job.

177
00:12:44,750 --> 00:12:47,140
My eyes hurt, my shoulders hurt,

178
00:12:47,140 --> 00:12:49,700
and my whole body hurts doing this.

179
00:12:49,700 --> 00:12:56,730
I didn't know sewing eyes on stuffed animals was this hard.

180
00:12:56,730 --> 00:13:01,070
Aigoo. Because I felt bad for Hyeon Cheol,

181
00:13:01,070 --> 00:13:03,650
I wanted to do something to help him.

182
00:13:03,650 --> 00:13:05,940
So, I sew 300 eyes every day—

183
00:13:05,940 --> 00:13:09,750
Mother, I'll get your medicine made later.

184
00:13:11,150 --> 00:13:17,040
 Gosh, what a bitch. She always says she'd get it for me "later." 

185
00:13:19,240 --> 00:13:21,330
Who is it?

186
00:13:24,250 --> 00:13:26,510
Gosh, Ae Gyo.

187
00:13:28,040 --> 00:13:30,940
What brings you to our house?

188
00:13:33,480 --> 00:13:38,300
Ae Gyo, what brings you to our house out of the blue?

189
00:13:38,300 --> 00:13:42,390
I thought of you while I was in the neighborhood.

190
00:13:42,390 --> 00:13:45,250
Am I not supposed to visit you or something?

191
00:13:45,250 --> 00:13:47,320
Of course, you can.

192
00:13:47,320 --> 00:13:51,810
I was just curious because you suddenly showed up without telling me.

193
00:13:51,810 --> 00:13:56,630
You were closer to me when we were in high school.

194
00:13:56,630 --> 00:14:00,440
But at some point, you started caring for Soo Yeon more.

195
00:14:00,440 --> 00:14:03,490
So, I was actually pretty disappointed, to be honest.

196
00:14:03,490 --> 00:14:07,430
Gosh, were you?

197
00:14:08,240 --> 00:14:13,020
We did grow apart since we lost touch at some point,

198
00:14:13,020 --> 00:14:15,750
but I feel bad since you're saying that.

199
00:14:15,750 --> 00:14:18,270
I didn't do it on purpose.

200
00:14:18,270 --> 00:14:21,320
Gosh, I was just saying that.

201
00:14:21,320 --> 00:14:25,350
Right. These are makeup products.

202
00:14:25,350 --> 00:14:27,200
I got you some while I was getting mine.

203
00:14:27,200 --> 00:14:30,310
Try using them. It's really nice.

204
00:14:30,310 --> 00:14:33,610
Ae Gyo, this is really expensive stuff.

205
00:14:33,610 --> 00:14:35,800
You shouldn't have.

206
00:14:35,800 --> 00:14:39,610
It's a gift from a rich friend. Can't you just take it?

207
00:14:39,610 --> 00:14:42,530
We need to care for our skin at our age.

208
00:14:42,530 --> 00:14:44,920
Otherwise, it suddenly gets ruined.

209
00:14:44,920 --> 00:14:48,530
Okay, thank you. I'll enjoy them.

210
00:14:48,530 --> 00:14:52,560
My skin is being well-treated, thanks to you.

211
00:14:54,060 --> 00:14:58,410
Maybe it's my age, but I think of my friends a lot these days.

212
00:14:58,410 --> 00:15:00,970
I think of the old memories, too.

213
00:15:00,970 --> 00:15:05,170
Do you remember when you, me, and Ji Hye went to Wolmi-do?

214
00:15:05,170 --> 00:15:09,130
Gosh, of course, I remember.

215
00:15:09,130 --> 00:15:13,310
We saw the ocean and went to a theme park, too.

216
00:15:13,310 --> 00:15:18,810
We barely managed to get home after getting drunk with dongdongju and pajeon.

217
00:15:18,810 --> 00:15:21,520
Yes, we did.

218
00:15:21,520 --> 00:15:24,140
The three of us were closer then.

219
00:15:24,140 --> 00:15:26,670
Since Soo Yeon was the daughter of an assemblyman and aloof,

220
00:15:26,670 --> 00:15:30,180
we didn't dare to even look at her.

221
00:15:31,520 --> 00:15:36,960
By the way, since when did you get close to her?

222
00:15:36,960 --> 00:15:43,250
I happened to run into her in the neighborhood after I had Pil Sung.

223
00:15:43,250 --> 00:15:47,650
I suppose her family used to live near here.

224
00:15:47,650 --> 00:15:52,250
She said she couldn't get pregnant and found Pil Sung so cute.

225
00:15:52,250 --> 00:15:54,640
So she stopped by often.

226
00:15:54,640 --> 00:15:57,100
That's how we got close.

227
00:15:58,010 --> 00:16:00,220
What do you mean?

228
00:16:00,220 --> 00:16:05,090
Didn't you say she gave you postnatal care since your mom passed?

229
00:16:05,090 --> 00:16:07,990
So, what do you mean you ran into her after giving birth?

230
00:16:07,990 --> 00:16:10,730
N-No, I mean...

231
00:16:10,730 --> 00:16:14,160
How long ago was that, anyway?

232
00:16:14,160 --> 00:16:19,240
I meant I ran into her when I was pregnant with him.

233
00:16:19,240 --> 00:16:23,410
She used to visit me often when I was pregnant.

234
00:16:23,410 --> 00:16:27,020
She cared for me a lot then.

235
00:16:27,020 --> 00:16:31,020
She helped me a lot with postnatal care, too.

236
00:16:31,020 --> 00:16:33,160
Is that so?

237
00:16:33,160 --> 00:16:37,820
By the way, who was Soo Yeon close to when we were in high school?

238
00:16:37,820 --> 00:16:41,600
Well, was she close to Eun Joo then?

239
00:16:41,600 --> 00:16:43,780
She probably was.

240
00:16:43,780 --> 00:16:46,330
I think she used to hang out with Eun Joo all the time.

241
00:16:46,330 --> 00:16:48,120
Oh, Kang Eun Joo?

242
00:16:48,120 --> 00:16:50,760
The one who moved to Busan after marrying someone from there?

243
00:16:50,760 --> 00:16:53,060
You're right.

244
00:16:53,060 --> 00:16:55,750
I think I saw them hanging out, too.

245
00:17:09,300 --> 00:17:11,250
 When Seon Yeong had a baby, 

246
00:17:11,250 --> 00:17:14,410
 I went to the hospital with her because her mother had passed away early on. 

247
00:17:14,410 --> 00:17:16,090
 I helped her with the postnatal care, too. 

248
00:17:16,090 --> 00:17:21,970
 I happened to run into her in the neighborhood after I had Pil Sung. 

249
00:17:21,970 --> 00:17:24,530
 N-No, I mean... 

250
00:17:24,530 --> 00:17:26,930
 How long ago was that, anyway? 

251
00:17:26,930 --> 00:17:32,440
 I meant I ran into her when I was pregnant with him. 

252
00:17:32,440 --> 00:17:34,640
Why do they say different things?

253
00:17:34,640 --> 00:17:36,920
How strange.

254
00:17:36,920 --> 00:17:40,140
No, I shouldn't be doing this right now.

255
00:17:40,140 --> 00:17:43,260
Eun Joo. Kang Eun Joo.

256
00:17:43,260 --> 00:17:45,490
Yes, there it is.

257
00:17:47,540 --> 00:17:51,520
Gosh, Eun Joo. It's me, Ae Gyo.

